# Exclude everything the docker daemon doesn't need to see.
#
# Docker uploads the WHOLE build context to the daemon before executing
# any Dockerfile instructions. Without this list a single `docker build`
# would ship 1-2 GB of build artefacts, vendored third-party sources,
# the .git history, and the Python venv -- slow over network, and they
# would silently invalidate the layer cache every time a build directory
# changed.
#
# Rule of thumb: if a path is not committed to git AND not in /src for a
# normal source tree, it does not belong in the image build.

# Build outputs -- the in-container build runs from scratch on a clean
# tree, never re-uses host artefacts.
build/
build-*/
out/
cmake-build-*/

# Vendor caches (open62541 / stb_image / etc. fetched by CMake FetchContent
# at host build time). The container's build stage fetches them fresh.
_deps/
.cache/

# Git -- the binary doesn't need history at runtime, and `git` is not
# installed in the runtime image anyway.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/

# Python venv used for the example scripts -- not part of the C++ build.
# `**/` so a nested venv (e.g. `scripts/ml/.venv/`) is excluded too;
# without the prefix the pattern would only match the top-level dir.
# The lib64 symlinks Linux venvs ship break Windows context uploads.
.venv/
**/.venv/
venv/
**/venv/
*.pyc
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/

# Docs / images / generated artefacts that don't influence the build.
docs/screenshots/
*.log

# Python ML pipeline scripts (export / quantize / benchmark a torchvision
# model into ONNX). Used at host development time, not by the C++ build
# and not at runtime. Excluding the whole tree avoids the nested venv +
# any future stray symlinks under it.
scripts/

# Example client scripts: they exercise the HMI over the wire, but the
# C++ build doesn't consume them. docker-compose mounts them separately
# when needed.
examples/

# IDE / editor scratch.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
.DS_Store

# Worktrees -- nested checkouts the harness leaves around. Definitely
# do not ship sibling branches into the image.
.claude/

# CHANGELOG and large markdown docs -- not used at runtime. Saves a few
# hundred KB on context upload; keep the binary lean.
CHANGELOG.md
*.md
!README.md
